# pii-scan allowlist — extended regexes for known-safe matches.
#
# scripts/pii-scan.sh matches by shape and will occasionally hit a
# placeholder or a documentation example. List those safe shapes here so the
# scanner stays quiet on a clean tree. Each line is an ERE tested against a
# "file:line:content" (tree) or "label:line:content" (message) string; a
# match drops the finding.
#
# Section markers are LOAD-BEARING: only entries under `# === BLOCKING` are
# consulted for blocking findings (private-key / aws-access-key-id). Advisory
# findings consult every entry. This is why a broad advisory entry can never
# silence a real key — put an entry under the wrong marker and it simply will
# not apply to the block tier.
#
# Keep BLOCKING entries NARROW — a broad allow rule silences a real leak.
# Advisory entries (db-url / email / home-path shapes) can be a little
# broader since advisory findings never fail a build; they only tune the
# daily review summary. Never add a real store name or credential here —
# that would put the very string we hide into a tracked, public file.
# Denylisted literals are matched separately and cannot be allowlisted.

# === BLOCKING-tier allows (keep narrow) ===================================
# Canonical synthetic AWS key ids always carry the word EXAMPLE.
AKIA[0-9A-Z]*EXAMPLE

# === Advisory-tier allows (documentation / test fixtures) ================
# --- placeholder / example email addresses --------------------------------
noreply@anthropic\.com
@users\.noreply\.github\.com
@example\.(com|org|net)
@.*\bexample\b
you@example
user@host
git@github\.com
# `victim.` marks a deliberately fake target host in security docs/tests.
@[A-Za-z0-9.-]*victim\.

# --- synthetic connection strings in tests / docs -------------------------
# Fixtures use example / *.supabase.co / *.neon.tech / dsql / localhost /
# db.internal hosts with throwaway credentials. Real credentials never live
# in a tracked file (they are in the OS keyring), so a passworded URL here is
# always a fixture.
(postgres|postgresql|mysql|libsql|mongodb)://[^ "']*@[^ "']*(example|supabase\.co|neon\.tech|dsql|\.on\.aws|localhost|127\.0\.0\.1|db\.internal|:memory:)
# Bare literal placeholder hosts and <angle-bracket> tokens in docs.
(postgres|postgresql|mysql|libsql|mongodb)://[^ "']*@host[:/ ]
(postgres|postgresql|mysql|libsql|mongodb)://[^ "']*<[A-Za-z]

# --- documentation / test home paths --------------------------------------
# `C:\path\to\...`, `C:\Users\you|<user>|USERNAME|me|alice` are docs/tests.
[Cc]:\\+[Uu]sers\\+(you|me|user|USERNAME|<user>|<name>|youruser|alice|bob|test)\b
